  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: Autumn Floods
---
The Lord of the River said, "Men who debate such matters these days all
claim that the minutest thing has no form and the largest thing cannot
be encompassed. Is this a true statement?"
